So I got some waffles. some biscuits.
I got some pancakes. I got some bacon.

734
00:42:15.120 --> 00:42:17.040
I got ham. I put a lot of butter on the ham.

735
00:42:17.130 --> 00:42:18.960
a lot of salt and pepper.
make it nice and flavourful.

736
00:42:19.050 --> 00:42:20.340
I got oatmeal on the stove.

737
00:42:20.420 --> 00:42:21.710
I got sausage.

738
00:42:21.800 --> 00:42:24.300
and I got eggs and grits and everything else.

739
00:42:24.380 --> 00:42:26.220
Y'all better just feast.

740
00:42:28.300 --> 00:42:29.890
It looks so good.

741
00:42:29.970 --> 00:42:32.850
It's a lot of carbs. You like carbs?

742
00:42:32.930 --> 00:42:34.270
- It's a lot of...
- Carbs.

743
00:42:34.390 --> 00:42:36.480
No. baby. I don't eat crabs.
You can't eat no crabs.

744
00:42:36.560 --> 00:42:39.310
You going to have crabs and yogurt?
You about to mess your stomach up.

745
00:42:39.400 --> 00:42:41.650
Ain't no seafood on here. honey.
I'm allergic to seafood.

746
00:42:41.730 --> 00:42:43.070
Ain't no seafood here nowhere.

747
00:42:43.150 --> 00:42:44.900
Is that how you stay so thin?

748
00:42:44.990 --> 00:42:47.530
No. honey. I don't eat that stuff.
Where your family?

749
00:42:47.620 --> 00:42:49.700
They're sleeping still.

750
00:42:49.780 --> 00:42:52.450
What? They got to get up.

751
00:42:53.000 --> 00:42:56.120
No. baby. your children got to go to school.
I got to get them registered.

752
00:42:56.250 --> 00:42:58.710
and George is supposed to see Brian
down at the attorney's office.

753
00:42:58.790 --> 00:43:00.590
So. no. no. no. you got to get them up.

754
00:43:00.670 --> 00:43:03.340
Okay. well. I was just going to let...
You know. they're so exhausted.

755
00:43:03.420 --> 00:43:05.670
- No. I'll go get them up. Here. you take this.
- Okay.

756
00:43:05.760 --> 00:43:06.970
Take this and stir that real good.

757
00:43:07.090 --> 00:43:09.140
- Whip it real. real good. You understand?
- Yeah. I understand.

758
00:43:09.260 --> 00:43:11.260
All right. you need to put something... Here.

759
00:43:11.350 --> 00:43:13.100
Here. put this on.
Put this on while you whip.

760
00:43:13.180 --> 00:43:14.680
- You don't want to get that on you.
- Okay. No.

761
00:43:14.770 --> 00:43:15.980
- Put that on. Okay. whip it.
- Thank you.

762
00:43:16.100 --> 00:43:18.150
- Whip it real good.
- I will.

763
00:43:23.360 --> 00:43:25.940
George. get up out this bed. son.

764
00:43:30.370 --> 00:43:31.530
Kate.

765
00:43:32.950 --> 00:43:35.290
I had this horrible dream

766
00:43:35.620 --> 00:43:39.080
that we were in trouble with the FBI.

767
00:43:39.170 --> 00:43:43.130
and we moved into this house
with an old woman who looked like...

768
00:43:44.710 --> 00:43:45.800
Like what?

769
00:43:46.880 --> 00:43:48.010
You.

770
00:43:49.050 --> 00:43:52.680
It's not a dream. It's really happening.

771
00:43:53.140 --> 00:43:54.850
I'm in so deep.

772
00:43:57.190 --> 00:44:00.310
George. you need to get up out this bed.
Brian is waiting for you down at the office.

773
00:44:00.400 --> 00:44:02.110
He said he was going to have you
come down there this morning.

774
00:44:02.190 --> 00:44:03.940
Now. get up on out this bed.

775
00:44:04.030 --> 00:44:07.190
My life is over.
I'm not getting out of this bed.

776
00:44:07.320 --> 00:44:09.530
There's no reason to get out of this bed.

777
00:44:09.660 --> 00:44:13.030
You need a reason? You need a reason?

778
00:44:15.240 --> 00:44:17.750
You better get your ass out this bed.

779
00:44:22.380 --> 00:44:24.750
Is that enough reason for you?

780
00:44:24.840 --> 00:44:25.920
Let me tell you something. son.

781
00:44:26.010 --> 00:44:29.010
I don't allow nobody to feel sorry
for themselves in my house.

782
00:44:29.090 --> 00:44:30.880
I don't know what you did.
I don't care what you did.

783
00:44:31.010 --> 00:44:32.010
Do you understand?

784
00:44:32.090 --> 00:44:33.680
I need you to get up out this bed.
come downstairs.

785
00:44:33.760 --> 00:44:36.600
have breakfast with your family.
Brian is waiting on you down at the office

786
00:44:36.680 --> 00:44:38.020
to talk about
whatever y'all need to talk about.

787
00:44:38.100 --> 00:44:41.480
It ain't my business. I don't want to know.
but you going to get up out this bed.

788
00:44:41.560 --> 00:44:43.440
If I come back up these stairs.
and you still in this bed.

789
00:44:43.520 --> 00:44:45.150
do you have any idea what I'm going to do?

790
00:44:45.230 --> 00:44:48.530
I'm going to get completely naked.
and get up in there with you and spoon.

791
00:44:49.740 --> 00:44:50.990
I'm up.

792
00:44:51.070 --> 00:44:52.070
Thank you.

793
00:44:52.200 --> 00:44:55.450
I am definitely up.
You don't have to come back.

794
00:44:55.540 --> 00:44:58.910
I'm coming right down.
I'm coming right down.

795
00:45:00.750 --> 00:45:02.370
I'm on my way.

796
00:45:13.510 --> 00:45:14.550
Get up. son.

797
00:45:17.390 --> 00:45:18.430
What's wrong?

798
00:45:19.390 --> 00:45:21.180
You just scared me.

799
00:45:21.270 --> 00:45:25.560
You're just so huge.
Like a giant bag of Skittles.

800
00:45:27.020 --> 00:45:29.320
All right. you better get the hell up.

801
00:45:29.400 --> 00:45:31.240
or when I come back up in here.
you know what's going to happen?

802
00:45:31.360 --> 00:45:33.740
You going to taste the rainbow.

803
00:45:34.140 --> 00:45:36.180
- Now. get up.
- I'm up. I'm up.

804
00:45:36.310 --> 00:45:39.520
Probably dreaming about Skittles
and Coca-Cola and Pepsi.

805
00:45:39.640 --> 00:45:41.980
diet soda and Mountain Dew
and Honey Buns.

806
00:45:42.060 --> 00:45:43.940
and damn Krispy Kreme and everything else.

807
00:45:44.020 --> 00:45:45.060
So you're up?

808
00:45:45.190 --> 00:45:48.690
There you are. Sadie.
You must iron the sheets.

809
00:45:48.820 --> 00:45:52.240
Mr. Needleman gets very angry
if there are any wrinkles.

810
00:45:54.870 --> 00:45:56.700
Honey. who the hell is Sadie?

811
00:45:56.830 --> 00:45:58.830
Don't you use that kind of language with me.

812
00:45:58.910 --> 00:46:02.330
'Cause I'll have you fired.
Do you understand?

813
00:46:02.420 --> 00:46:05.250
Mrs. Needleman. Okay. I get it.

814
00:46:05.380 --> 00:46:09.380
The mall is open. but there
ain't nobody in their shopping.

815
00:46:11.170 --> 00:46:12.300
What's that smell?

816
00:46:12.380 --> 00:46:14.890
It's called food. I'm cooking.

817
00:46:15.010 --> 00:46:18.010
It smells up the whole house. It permeates.

818
00:46:18.100 --> 00:46:22.890
Thank you. You always were
the best colored help we could ever find.

819
00:46:25.230 --> 00:46:28.020
Okay. Brian playing a joke on me.

820
00:46:28.110 --> 00:46:31.490
I'm being Punk'd. I know I'm being Punk'd.
Where the camera at?

821
00:46:31.570 --> 00:46:33.530
Little girl. I need you to get up. honey.

822
00:46:33.610 --> 00:46:35.410
Go away.

823
00:46:40.950 --> 00:46:44.960
Never had no child talk to me
like this before. Lordy.

824
00:46:45.080 --> 00:46:48.960
Honey. I got to bring y'all down to school
and get you registered. Now. get up.

825
00:46:51.090 --> 00:46:52.880
I said. go away.

826
00:46:55.470 --> 00:46:58.600
She just yelled at me in my house.
I don't know what she...

827
00:46:58.720 --> 00:47:00.010
Little girl.
I'm going to tell you one more time...

828
00:47:00.100 --> 00:47:02.140
I said. go away!

829
00:47:09.940 --> 00:47:11.730
I know she didn't just...

830
00:47:16.910 --> 00:47:18.910
Who the hell you think
you talking to?

831
00:47:20.910 --> 00:47:23.830
Oh. my God! What is wrong with you?

832
00:47:23.960 --> 00:47:26.000
This is my house.

833
00:47:26.120 --> 00:47:28.630
You live by my rules
when you are in my house.

834
00:47:28.750 --> 00:47:30.920
You're too young for that. little girl.
You don't want none of this.

835
00:47:31.000 --> 00:47:35.010
Please. do yourself a favour. honey.
You do not want none of this.

836
00:47:35.130 --> 00:47:38.180
Behave while you're here. If not. you will...

837
00:47:41.640 --> 00:47:43.770
GirI. you...

838
00:47:43.850 --> 00:47:46.440
GirI. you just don't know...

839
00:47:50.190 --> 00:47:52.150
I don't know who she thinks
she's talking to.

840
00:47:52.480 --> 00:47:53.940
She's insane.

841
00:47:58.450 --> 00:47:59.450
Hello?

842
00:48:00.200 --> 00:48:01.370
Is that you. son?

843
00:48:04.000 --> 00:48:06.330
- Yes. sir.
- Well. come on in here.

844
00:48:08.540 --> 00:48:10.210
What are you doing here. Dad?

845
00:48:10.920 --> 00:48:13.090
Well. I'm feeling better. much better.

846
00:48:13.210 --> 00:48:17.260
No. you're not.
You're supposed to be at home in bed.

847
00:48:17.380 --> 00:48:21.430
I just had to stop by here
to make sure everything's all right.

848
00:48:21.930 --> 00:48:22.930
It's all fine.

849
00:48:23.430 --> 00:48:29.190
I've decided to tell the church
the third Sunday I'm retiring.

850
00:48:29.650 --> 00:48:31.650
I thought you were going to wait
till summer to do that.

851
00:48:31.770 --> 00:48:35.190
No. I can't do that. son. I'm too tired.

852
00:48:35.280 --> 00:48:37.700
It'll sure make the burden so much easier

853
00:48:37.780 --> 00:48:42.740
to know that everything I've worked for
all these years is going to be looked after.

854
00:48:42.830 --> 00:48:46.120
I am very proud of you. son.
Really proud of you.

855
00:48:47.460 --> 00:48:49.370
Don't be proud of me.

856
00:48:49.460 --> 00:48:52.000
Are you kidding me?
I have to tell you I'm proud of you.

857
00:48:52.130 --> 00:48:55.250
You know something?
After your mother died.

858
00:48:55.340 --> 00:48:56.630
I wasn't sure you were going to make it.

859
00:48:57.670 --> 00:49:00.760
You were so far out there in those streets.

860
00:49:00.840 --> 00:49:02.680
But. praise the Lord. look at you now.

861
00:49:02.810 --> 00:49:07.430
Helping me run the church.
handling our mortgage payment fund.

862
00:49:07.520 --> 00:49:09.140
No. I am very proud of you. son.

863
00:49:09.560 --> 00:49:11.940
You know. the congregation
is going to be a little bit upset

864
00:49:12.020 --> 00:49:15.980
when I tell them that I'm retiring.
so to ease the pain.

865
00:49:16.070 --> 00:49:20.200
I'm going to tell them that we have raised
the money to pay off the church.

866
00:49:21.700 --> 00:49:23.450
They're going to rejoice.

867
00:49:24.830 --> 00:49:26.290
Well done. son.

868
00:49:26.370 --> 00:49:27.700
Yes. sir.

869
00:49:37.010 --> 00:49:40.420
I don't see her out here. Y'all come on.
Come on. Hurry up.

870
00:49:40.510 --> 00:49:43.890
She always nosy as hell.
over there looking at everything.

871
00:49:43.970 --> 00:49:45.350
Hurry up.

872
00:49:50.390 --> 00:49:52.980
- Come on. Get in the car.
- Madea.

873
00:49:53.060 --> 00:49:54.230
Madea.

874
00:49:54.440 --> 00:49:55.570
Hey. Hattie.

875
00:49:56.530 --> 00:49:57.690
How you doing?

876
00:49:57.780 --> 00:49:59.070
- I'm good. baby.
- Open the door.

877
00:49:59.150 --> 00:50:01.780
- Come here a minute.
- I can't talk to you right now. honey.

878
00:50:01.860 --> 00:50:04.780
This my cousins. and they done lost
all the pigmentation in their skin overnight.

879
00:50:04.870 --> 00:50:06.160
- Your cousins?
- Yes.

880
00:50:06.240 --> 00:50:07.240
Can I help you?

881
00:50:07.330 --> 00:50:09.750
No. I got to take them
to the doctor right now.

882
00:50:09.830 --> 00:50:12.040
I'll see you later on. Take care.

883
00:50:16.800 --> 00:50:18.550
And that's all you know?

884
00:50:18.630 --> 00:50:20.920
That's all I know. I swear it.

885
00:50:21.260 --> 00:50:22.550
I don't believe you.

886
00:50:23.640 --> 00:50:25.720
I'm telling you the truth.

887
00:50:26.140 --> 00:50:29.140
You're going to jail for a very long time.

888
00:50:34.860 --> 00:50:39.150
I can't go to jail. I didn't do anything wrong.

889
00:50:39.230 --> 00:50:41.610
George. calm down. okay?

890
00:50:42.280 --> 00:50:45.360
For what it's worth. I believe you.

891
00:50:46.370 --> 00:50:50.410
Oh. boy. somebody believes me.
Isn't that wonderful?

892
00:50:50.500 --> 00:50:55.040
Let's crack open some champagne.
because somebody believes me.

893
00:50:56.000 --> 00:50:57.920
Oh. God. I'm in trouble.

894
00:51:01.420 --> 00:51:05.930
I think they can believe you. too.
but you have to help me make them believe.

895
00:51:06.680 --> 00:51:10.850
Just tell me what you want me to do.

896
00:51:10.930 --> 00:51:13.730
What do I need to do here?

897
00:51:13.810 --> 00:51:16.560
Okay. that's a good attitude. George.
Really good attitude.

898
00:51:16.650 --> 00:51:19.520
Everything that wasn't shredded
or destroyed is in these files.

899
00:51:19.610 --> 00:51:23.690
This is your ticket to freedom.
You're the CFO. I'm sure you can find it.

900
00:51:24.450 --> 00:51:25.660
Okay. well.

901
00:51:25.910 --> 00:51:30.490
this is the crux of the problem here. Brian.

902
00:51:30.580 --> 00:51:35.710
because I can't seem to find anything
in here that will help.

903
00:51:35.790 --> 00:51:37.670
I want to help you. I really do.

904
00:51:37.750 --> 00:51:42.000
It doesn't make any sense
for me not to want to help.

905
00:51:42.090 --> 00:51:44.800
Now does it? Does it? No. No.

906
00:51:44.880 --> 00:51:48.340
I mean. don't you think
I would help if I could?

907
00:51:52.100 --> 00:51:53.980
- Are you okay?
- No. I just...

908
00:51:54.060 --> 00:51:56.940
I feel like I... I want to hit something.

909
00:51:57.020 --> 00:51:58.850
Hit the chair. Hit something.

910
00:52:09.450 --> 00:52:10.490
I'm sorry.

911
00:52:26.340 --> 00:52:28.430
That was a lovely evening.

912
00:52:30.350 --> 00:52:32.850
There ain't never been no evening. lady.
I don't know you.

913
00:52:33.350 --> 00:52:37.270
Stop it. There's no one around.

914
00:52:37.350 --> 00:52:40.350
Read my lips. honey. I don't know you.

915
00:52:41.310 --> 00:52:43.860
You're the man in the boat.

916
00:52:43.980 --> 00:52:46.030
I ain't never had no boat.

917
00:52:49.820 --> 00:52:53.620
I bet if I showed you my tattoo.
you might remember.

918
00:52:53.700 --> 00:52:56.500
What tattoo? What you fixing to show me?

919
00:53:01.380 --> 00:53:04.050
I believe you need to see a doctor
about that. honey.

920
00:53:04.130 --> 00:53:07.380
No. that's Betty Boop.

921
00:53:09.380 --> 00:53:13.470
It might have been Betty Boop at one time.
but Betty Boop done drooped.

922
00:53:13.560 --> 00:53:15.140
Betty Boop.

923
00:53:15.220 --> 00:53:17.890
You brought me over in your little boat.

924
00:53:18.020 --> 00:53:23.230
Lady. for the last time. okay?
First of all. you insulted me.

925
00:53:23.320 --> 00:53:24.650
'Cause I wouldn't have a little boat.

926
00:53:24.730 --> 00:53:27.150
I'm not a canoe kind of man.
You understand?

927
00:53:27.240 --> 00:53:30.990
I'm a yacht. a cruise ship.
Noah's Ark up in this piece.

928
00:53:31.070 --> 00:53:34.240
Only time I was ever in a boat was
that little rowboat belonged to the Army

929
00:53:34.370 --> 00:53:36.240
when I was in New Orleans many years ago.

930
00:53:36.330 --> 00:53:39.500
I'd take people across the water
over there from the bayou to the juke joint.

931
00:53:39.580 --> 00:53:41.000
and I'd charge them a nickeI
to get them over there.

932
00:53:41.080 --> 00:53:43.500
And they'd all take the ride and everything.
I'd give them their change.

933
00:53:43.590 --> 00:53:46.920
And somebody gave me a 50-cent tip
that night.

934
00:53:52.510 --> 00:53:54.010
You Barbara Betty Boop.

935
00:53:54.100 --> 00:53:57.930
Yes. I was a nurse in Company B.

936
00:53:59.940 --> 00:54:03.100
Yeah. I was in Company C
over there with the colored troops.

937
00:54:03.230 --> 00:54:06.940
Me and a couple of my girlfriends followed
you guys all the way to your barracks.

938
00:54:07.070 --> 00:54:09.440
Yeah. I remember it was four of you.

939
00:54:09.570 --> 00:54:15.870
It was Blanche. Rose. Dorothy. and you.

940
00:54:19.120 --> 00:54:20.700
I don't even know
how you remember that. honey.

941
00:54:20.790 --> 00:54:23.710
That was 56. 57 years ago.

942
00:54:23.790 --> 00:54:25.880
Fifty-three.

943
00:54:25.960 --> 00:54:28.090
Because George is 52.

944
00:54:30.470 --> 00:54:32.380
What that got to do with anything?

945
00:54:34.800 --> 00:54:37.050
What day is it?

946
00:54:37.560 --> 00:54:41.100
Lady. don't you start...
What you trying to tell me?

947
00:54:43.100 --> 00:54:44.480
Where am I?

948
00:54:44.560 --> 00:54:47.230
I think you believe you're trying
to tell me something about George.

949
00:54:47.320 --> 00:54:49.070
- Oh. my goodness.
- Hey.

950
00:54:49.150 --> 00:54:50.900
I don't know where I am.

951
00:54:57.330 --> 00:54:58.620
George?

952
00:55:02.500 --> 00:55:03.580
- Brian.
- Jake.

953
00:55:03.670 --> 00:55:05.500
You cannot keep calling me like this. man.

954
00:55:05.630 --> 00:55:07.460
I'm in the middle of an investigation.
What are you doing?

955
00:55:08.090 --> 00:55:11.340
My dad wants to announce that he's paying
the church's mortgage off in three weeks.

956
00:55:11.420 --> 00:55:13.010
I mean. what am I supposed to do?

957
00:55:13.130 --> 00:55:14.840
Tell him the truth.

958
00:55:14.970 --> 00:55:16.010
That will kill him.

959
00:55:16.090 --> 00:55:18.430
He'll be very happy
that you told him the truth.

960
00:55:18.510 --> 00:55:20.100
I can't. I can't do it.

961
00:55:20.180 --> 00:55:21.430
Jake.

962
00:55:21.520 --> 00:55:23.520
That's him. That's the dude from the news!

963
00:55:24.190 --> 00:55:25.440
I ought to kill you!

964
00:55:25.520 --> 00:55:27.860
- Who is this?
- I'm your worst nightmare.

965
00:55:27.980 --> 00:55:29.270
Will you just...

966
00:55:29.360 --> 00:55:33.360
You're my worst... I got news for you.
I'm living my worst nightmare. okay?

967
00:55:33.490 --> 00:55:36.530
And besides. you're a little short
to be a nightmare. aren't you?

968
00:55:36.620 --> 00:55:39.200
I'm short? He called me...
He called me short?

969
00:55:39.280 --> 00:55:40.870
I'm going to bust your balls!

970
00:55:40.950 --> 00:55:44.370
Well. why don't you get in line
and bust my balls?

